```python
def remove_repeat_chars(string):
    return string[:70] + ''.join([char for char in string[70:98] if string[70:98].count(char) == 1]) + string[98:]
```
Note: The given code snippet removes all occurrences of characters that occur more than once between the indices 70 and 98 (both exclusive) in the given string, while preserving the order of all other characters in the string.
